  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 11th level, a mesmerist can deceive truthdetecting magic. A creature using this sort of magic against the mesmerist must succeed at a caster level check against a DC of 15 + the mesmerist’s class level to succeed (as if the mesmerist were under the effect of a&nbsp;glibness&nbsp;spell); failure means the magic doesn’t detect the mesmerist’s lies or force him to speak only the truth. This ability does not give the mesmerist the&nbsp;glibness&nbsp;spell’s bonus on Bluff checks.</p>",
